Kenya Meteorological Director Stella Aura has said that some parts of the country will receive light rains for the five forecasted days. In a statement on Wednesday, Aura said that rainfall is expected over a few areas in the Lake Victoria Basin, the Highlands West of the Rift Valley, the Central and South Rift Valley, and the Highlands East of the Rift Valley and the Northeast. There will be rains over a few places in the counties of Turkana, West Pokot, and Samburu while the highlands East of the Rift Valley including Nairobi will have a chance of rains over a few places. Sunny intervals will be experienced in the South-eastern lowlands, except on Saturday where there will be a chance of rains over a few places. The northeast region (Marsabit, Mandera, Wajir, Garissa, and Isiolo will also experience rains over a few places. There will be a chance of showers over a few places in the Coastal strip region. Earlier on, the department had predicted that Nairobi is among counties likely to experience flash floods during the long rains season. It also warned that flash floods are very likely to occur in the Lake Victoria Basin, the highlands West of the Rift Valley, the Central Rift Valley and the highlands East of the Rift Valley due to the expected rainfall in these areas. The March-May 2021 long rains weather outlook indicated that slippery roads and poor visibility during rainstorms may also pose a danger to motorists and pedestrians, especially along the Kikuyu-Kinungi stretch on the Nakuru-Nairobi highway.